{"questionId":"22649586","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>70</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>70</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>73</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>45</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>73</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>45</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through within the question from their (labelled) value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>, when finding <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> (applies both if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> is incorrect or correct to a different level of accuracy).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22649586","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.1a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Determine the values of a, b and c.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.2—Histograms, CF graphs, box plots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"s